Program: Outlook
Title: MP Turns Ebola Ambulance Driver
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p029nlyp
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 6 Nov 2014
Liberian MP Saah Joseph imported six ambulances just before the ebola epidemic struck. Matthew Bannister hears how they have become a vital tool in helping Ebola patients. (Picture: One of Liberian MP Saah Joseph's Ebola ambulances)